<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="465" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1362,2037]" pageId="1" pageNumber="465">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1434,1460]" pageId="1" pageNumber="465">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Generally blackish brown; face black; antennal scape and pedicel subequal in length; apex of first flagellomere not produced beyond base of arista; arista laterally compressed and very high, arising at apex of first flagellomere and 2 times as long as latter; wing with broad, transverse, dark band at level of posterior crossvein; fore and mid leg with femur dark brown except base and apex narrowly yellowish, tibia and tarsus yellowish; hind femur and tibia generally dark brown, hind tarsus light brown; segment 8 of female with shallowly emarginated posterodorsal margin and deeply incised posteroventral margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="467" pageId="1" pageNumber="465" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1362,2037]" pageId="1" pageNumber="465">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,373,1650,1676]" pageId="1" pageNumber="465">Redescription.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[533,639,1651,1677]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3599999999999999" pageId="1" pageNumber="465" unit="mm" value="13.6">13.6 mm</quantity>
; wing length 
<quantity box="[800,892,1650,1677]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="465" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
; length of antenna 
<quantity box="[1117,1209,1651,1677]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="465" unit="mm" value="3.4">3.4 mm</quantity>
. Generally blackish brown, moderately shining. Frontal vitta and face black, gena slightly paler (
<figureCitation box="[1012,1113,1686,1713]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,489,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1436,489,1549]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–10. Terarista fujiana Wang, 1999 [Loxocera (Loxocera) fujiana (Wang, 1999), comb. nov.], ♀, lectotype: 4 head, dorsal; 5 same, lateral; 6 left antenna, dorsal; 7 same, lateral; 8 thorax, dorsal; 9 left wing, dorsal; 10 female terminalia, lateral. Scale bar 1.0 mm. Abbreviations: ce = cercus; s10 = sternite 10; t10 = tergite 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899812" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899812/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="465">Figs 4, 5</figureCitation>
); antennal scape and pedicel dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[296,399,1723,1749]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,489,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1436,489,1549]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–10. Terarista fujiana Wang, 1999 [Loxocera (Loxocera) fujiana (Wang, 1999), comb. nov.], ♀, lectotype: 4 head, dorsal; 5 same, lateral; 6 left antenna, dorsal; 7 same, lateral; 8 thorax, dorsal; 9 left wing, dorsal; 10 female terminalia, lateral. Scale bar 1.0 mm. Abbreviations: ce = cercus; s10 = sternite 10; t10 = tergite 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899812" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899812/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="465">Figs 6, 7</figureCitation>
); proboscis and palpus brown. Wing infumate, with broad, transverse, dark band at level of posterior crossvein, band more or less interrupted along center of cells r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[952,978,1777,1791]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="465">4+5</subScript>
and dm; apical margin of wing darkened between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[269,294,1813,1827]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="465">2+3</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[373,381,1813,1827]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="465">1</subScript>
; wing veins yellowish brown to brown (
<figureCitation box="[829,897,1795,1821]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,489,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1436,489,1549]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–10. Terarista fujiana Wang, 1999 [Loxocera (Loxocera) fujiana (Wang, 1999), comb. nov.], ♀, lectotype: 4 head, dorsal; 5 same, lateral; 6 left antenna, dorsal; 7 same, lateral; 8 thorax, dorsal; 9 left wing, dorsal; 10 female terminalia, lateral. Scale bar 1.0 mm. Abbreviations: ce = cercus; s10 = sternite 10; t10 = tergite 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899812" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899812/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="465">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Halter whitish yellow with base darkened. Leg dark brown; trochanter and hind tarsus light brown; base and apex of fore and mid femur, fore and mid tibia and tarsus yellowish brown. Abdomen black; segments 2–4 and terminalia of female reddish brown. Bristles on head and thorax black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1362,2037]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,573]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="466" pageId="1" pageNumber="465">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[274,375,1938,1965]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,489,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1436,489,1549]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–10. Terarista fujiana Wang, 1999 [Loxocera (Loxocera) fujiana (Wang, 1999), comb. nov.], ♀, lectotype: 4 head, dorsal; 5 same, lateral; 6 left antenna, dorsal; 7 same, lateral; 8 thorax, dorsal; 9 left wing, dorsal; 10 female terminalia, lateral. Scale bar 1.0 mm. Abbreviations: ce = cercus; s10 = sternite 10; t10 = tergite 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899812" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899812/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="465">Figs 4, 5</figureCitation>
) transverse oblong in dorsal view, largely glabrous; length along midline 0.8 times as long as width across eyes, width across eyes 1.9 times as broad as interocular space. Frons slightly protruding beyond level of anterior eye margin; frontal vitta desclerotized, dull and velvety, with deep depression at middle; frontal orbit with some scattered, erect, short hairs, middle one slightly longer than others, anterior portion near anterior margin with a narrow patch of golden tomentose. Lunule sclerotized, broadly exposed between antennal base and anterior margin of frons. Ocellar triangle broad, smooth, with silvery tomentose stripes along lateral margins. Face strongly slanting, with moderately-elevated median carina, each side with an elongate silvery tomentose patch. Parafacial narrow, with a tomentose golden patch between anterior eye margin and lunule. Gena slightly swollen; postgena covered with silvery tomentum. Occiput with a large silvery tomentose patch at middle above foramen. 1 ocellar bristle, weakly developed; postvertical, inner vertical and outer vertical bristle poorly differentiated. Antenna (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 4–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,489,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1436,489,1549]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–10. Terarista fujiana Wang, 1999 [Loxocera (Loxocera) fujiana (Wang, 1999), comb. nov.], ♀, lectotype: 4 head, dorsal; 5 same, lateral; 6 left antenna, dorsal; 7 same, lateral; 8 thorax, dorsal; 9 left wing, dorsal; 10 female terminalia, lateral. Scale bar 1.0 mm. Abbreviations: ce = cercus; s10 = sternite 10; t10 = tergite 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899812" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899812/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="466">Figs 6, 7</figureCitation>
) long and thick, with dense, decumbent, short setulae, and with setae oblique and short; scape nearly as long as pedicel, gradually widened towards apex of segment; first flagellomere about 2.3 times as long as pedicel, apex very weakly curving ventrally; arista laterally compressed and very high, arising at apex of first flagellomere, 2 times as long as first flagellomere, divided into small aristomere 1 and large aristomeres 2+3. Palpus elongate oval, with dense, decumbent, short golden setulae and scattered, long, black setae.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899810" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6899810" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899810/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="466" startId="2.[151,264,1584,1608]" targetBox="[161,1421,601,1547]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1584,1645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="466">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,315,1584,1609]" pageId="2" pageNumber="466">FIGURES 1–3.</emphasis>
