<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1691,2041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="466">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[296,363,1691,1717]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,489,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1436,489,1549]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–10. Terarista fujiana Wang, 1999 [Loxocera (Loxocera) fujiana (Wang, 1999), comb. nov.], ♀, lectotype: 4 head, dorsal; 5 same, lateral; 6 left antenna, dorsal; 7 same, lateral; 8 thorax, dorsal; 9 left wing, dorsal; 10 female terminalia, lateral. Scale bar 1.0 mm. Abbreviations: ce = cercus; s10 = sternite 10; t10 = tergite 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899812" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899812/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="466">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) robust, with dense, short, whitish yellow setulae except anepisternum (anterior half), anepimeron, katatergite, meron, scutellum and mediotergite (middle portion) glabrous; postpronotal lobe, anatergite and mediotergite (lateral portions) with fine tomentum; anepisternum (posterior half) and disc of scutellum with fine wrinkles. Scutum 1.45 times as long as wide, slightly swollen on anterior half and flattened on posterior half, with shallow rectangular depression posteriad of indistinct transverse suture. Scutellum subtriangular, slightly swollen and wider than long. 1 dorsocentral, 1 notopleural, 2 posterior supra-alar, 1 apical scutellar. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[1257,1325,1871,1897]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,489,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1436,489,1549]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–10. Terarista fujiana Wang, 1999 [Loxocera (Loxocera) fujiana (Wang, 1999), comb. nov.], ♀, lectotype: 4 head, dorsal; 5 same, lateral; 6 left antenna, dorsal; 7 same, lateral; 8 thorax, dorsal; 9 left wing, dorsal; 10 female terminalia, lateral. Scale bar 1.0 mm. Abbreviations: ce = cercus; s10 = sternite 10; t10 = tergite 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899812" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899812/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="466">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) with last sector of M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[278,286,1925,1939]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="466">1</subScript>
with strong curvature; apex of M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[654,662,1925,1939]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="466">4</subScript>
nearly reaching wing margin. Leg with dense, decumbent to suberect, whitish yellow setulae, except ventral surface of fore and mid femur largely glabrous; femur subfusiform, slightly compressed laterally, hind femur with a subapical patch of microtomentum on ventral surface; tibia gradually widened towards apex of segment, fore and mid tibia straight, hind tibia finely curved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="467">Abdomen elongate, with dense, decumbent, short, whitish yellow and black setae; syntergite 1+2 with several long hair-like setae laterally.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="467">
Female terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[422,506,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–10" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[162,1436,489,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1436,489,1549]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 4–10. Terarista fujiana Wang, 1999 [Loxocera (Loxocera) fujiana (Wang, 1999), comb. nov.], ♀, lectotype: 4 head, dorsal; 5 same, lateral; 6 left antenna, dorsal; 7 same, lateral; 8 thorax, dorsal; 9 left wing, dorsal; 10 female terminalia, lateral. Scale bar 1.0 mm. Abbreviations: ce = cercus; s10 = sternite 10; t10 = tergite 10." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899812" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899812/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="467">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) strongly sclerotized and laterally compressed. Basal half of tergite 7 with some shallow, widely separated transverse wrinkles; sternite 7 keeled along midline. Segment 8 coriaceous and longitudinally striate, posterodorsal margin shallowly emarginate, posterolateral margin forming acute angular protrusion, posteroventral margin with deep linear incision. Tergite and sternite 10 and cerci with scattered tiny setulae; lateral parts of tergite and sternite 10 and posterior margin of cerci with rows of long setae; cerci relatively broad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,465]" box="[199,376,403,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="467">Male unknown.</paragraph>
